================================================================
KEY TAKEAWAYS
================================================================
 
1. CATALOG DOMINANCE
   Sweet Tooth is the largest department (12,513 SKUs / ~19.7%).
   Cold Drinks and Juices is the largest single category (7,496).
   NOICE is the top brand by listing count (1,567), ahead of Amul.
 
2. DISCOUNT STRATEGY IS INVERTED
   Staple categories (Atta, Rice & Dal) are discounted most (22.02%).
   High-volume impulse categories (Sweet Tooth, Cold Drinks) are
   discounted least (11.43% and 12.08%), likely due to high demand.
 
3. CRITICAL AVAILABILITY PROBLEM IN FOOD CATEGORIES
   Ice Creams and Frozen Desserts has a 52.34% OOS rate — over half
   the SKUs listed are unavailable. Cold Drinks (48.24%), Dairy
   (45.96%), and Biscuits (44.99%) also exceed 44% OOS rates.
   Personal care categories (Skincare 22.29%, Makeup 24.41%) show
   far better availability.
 
4. PRICE AND DISCOUNT ARE DECOUPLED
   Correlation between product_price and discount_in_percent is -0.00.
   Discounting is a brand/category strategy, not a price-driven one.
 
5. LOCATION INFLUENCES PRICING AND PROMOTIONS
   Both store-level and pin code-level analysis show variation in
   average price and discount, indicating zone-based pricing by
   Swiggy Instamart.
 
6. PRICE COLUMNS ARE REDUNDANT
   item_selling_price and product_price correlate at 1.00.
   For modeling or reporting, one of these columns is sufficient.
 
